That's right,  California requires a "Visual Inspection" that requires ALL
of the stock stuff (ie: Fuel Injection, stock distributor, etc.,) be there,
otherwise you don't pass even if the sniff test is ZERO emissions ;-)

Now if it was a '75 (or earlier), there is no test required.
